data.description: Hurry! Beautiful historic Sears kit craftsman home awaits a new owner! Featured on the 2012 Historic House Walk, this home has character inside and out! Nestled on an deep, oversized corner fenced lot with quick access to train station and major highways for commuters! Front patio is perfect for summer nights! Warm inviting living room with cozy brick fireplace, custom built-ins, crown molding and gleaming hardwood floors! Bright open kitchen with oak cabinetry, pendant lighting and breakfast bar! Separate formal dining room with crown molding and direct pass thru to the kitchen and French door to the rear porch! Adorable sun porch great for sitting in those quiet moments also with sliding glass door to the custom deck (deck boards currently being replaced) Gracious size bedrooms with crown molding, built-ins and hardwood floors! Upgraded hall bath with whirlpool tub, wainscoting, chair rail and pedestal sink! Full basement with an extra bath and plenty of room for all your storage needs! New roof and gutters '23! Updated electrical! Exterior painted '23! Fence '22! Brick tuckpointed '22! New deck boards being installed! Storage shed! Some extras: new Sears attic fan in box, 2 vintage ceiling lights, clock from historical Elgin Clock Factory! Close to shopping and schools! This vintage home is a real charmer! Bring an offer today!
